cs.NE, cs.ET, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SY

This paper discusses the implementation of spiking neural networks in dynamic neuromorphic processors for feature detection and learning, which falls under the category of neural networks and machine learning. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also focuses on the use of delay mechanisms and coincidence detection, which are relevant to the sub-categories of cs.ET (Emerging Technologies) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of synapse weights and input noise, which are relevant to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
